<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Blessings everyone.<p>

To everyone who is about to make a new character:<br>
Why bother so much about stats when creating a character?<br>
You will be playing the character for a long time, if you choose a race you will enjoy roleplaying. If you choose a race you will dislike just for the stats, you probably won't play that character for very long.<p>

Stats can be modified with items, I guess you can add up to around 50 points to a stat in the long run. I have never cared much for numbers :) <p>

So play your favourite race and class, and stop caring about the stats. This is a roleplaying game after all.<br>
You'll have a lot of fun even though your wisdom or strength "could have been 5 points higher".<p>

Open your mind,<br>
Ellie</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
