<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">well...i agree with one thing, chose a race that you will enjoy playing, but i have to dissagree with not caring about stats.  for a cleric, the most important stat is wisdom.  more wisdom equals more mana which you makes you more effective as a cleric.  i would say start your wisdom at least at 100 and if you can try 115.  and all the other stats will be increase with items that will add wisdom too, so no worries on those.  i have a human cleric with a base wisdom of 90 and i have every slot, except the belt slot, filled with a +wisdom item and my current wisdon is only 184.  the only other item i could get would be a reed belt which would add 5 more wisdom which would put me at 189 wis.  i doubt that my wis will ever reach 200 which would give the most mana.  more wisdom really does make a difference.  i just aquired a pair of golden efreeti boots which added 9 wis and i noticed a definate mana increase, even at L53<p>

just this cleric's opinion<br>
-revbufbox, L53 vicar</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
